('G4426','G','πτύρω','ptýrō','ptoo''-ro','','to  frighten',':--terrify.'),
('G4427','G','πτύσμα','ptýsma','ptoos''-mah','','saliva',':--spittle.'),
('G4428','G','πτύσσω','ptýssō','ptoos''-so','','and thus apparently allied to   through the idea of expansion, and to 4429 through that of  flattening; compare ); to fold, i.e. furl a scroll',':--close.'),
('G4429','G','πτύω','ptýō','ptoo''-o','','to spit',':--spit.'),
('G4430','G','πτῶμα','ptōma','pto''-mah','','a ruin, i.e. (specially), lifeless body  (corpse, carrion)',':--dead body, carcase, corpse.'),
('G4431','G','πτῶσις','ptōsis','pto''-sis','','a crash, i.e. downfall (literally or  figuratively)',':--fall.'),
('G4432','G','πτωχεία','ptōcheía','pto-khi''-ah','','beggary, i.e. indigence (literally or  figuratively)',':--poverty.'),
('G4433','G','πτωχεύω','ptōcheúō','pto-khyoo''-o','','to be a beggar, i.e. (by implication) to become indigent  (figuratively)',':--become poor.'),
('G4434','G','πτωχός','ptōchós','pto-khos''','','akin to  and the alternate of ); a  beggar (as cringing), i.e. pauper (strictly denoting absolute or  public mendicancy, although also used in a qualified or relative  sense; whereas  properly means only straitened circumstances in  private), literally (often as noun) or figuratively  (distressed)',':--beggar(-ly), poor.'),
('G4435','G','πυγμή','pygmḗ','poog-may''','','the clenched hand, i.e.  (only in dative case as adverb) with the fist (hard scrubbing)',':--oft.'),
('G4436','G','Πύθων','Pýthōn','poo''-thone','','a Python, i.e. (by analogy, with the  supposed diviner there) inspiration (soothsaying)',':-- divination.'),
('G4437','G','πυκνός','pyknós','pook-nos''','','clasped (thick), i.e. (figuratively) frequent;  neuter plural (as adverb) frequently',':--often(-er).'),
('G4438','G','πυκτέω','pyktéō','pook-teh''-o','','to box (with the fist), i.e.  contend (as a boxer) at the games (figuratively)',':--fight.'),
('G4439','G','πύλη','pýlē','poo''-lay','','a gate, i.e. the leaf or wing of a folding  entrance (literally or figuratively)',':--gate.'),
('G4440','G','πυλών','pylṓn','poo-lone''','','a gate-way, door-way of a building or city; by implication,  a portal or vestibule',':--gate, porch.'),
('G4441','G','πυνθάνομαι','pynthánomai','poon-than''-om-ahee','','to question, i.e. ascertain by inquiry  (as a matter of information merely; and thus differing from ,  which properly means a request as a favor; and from , which is  strictly a demand for something due; as well as from , which  implies a search for something hidden; and from , which involves  the idea of urgent need); by implication, to learn (by casual  intelligence)',':--ask, demand, enquire, understand.'),
('G4442','G','πῦρ','pŷr','poor','','"fire" (literally or figuratively, specially,  lightning)',':--fiery, fire.'),
('G4443','G','πυρά','pyrá','poo-rah''','','a fire (concretely)',':--fire.'),
('G4444','G','πύργος','pýrgos','poor''-gos','','a tower or castle',':--tower.'),
('G4445','G','πυρέσσω','pyréssō','poo-res''-so','','to be on fire, i.e. (specially), to have a fever',':--be sick  of a fever.'),
('G4446','G','πυρετός','pyretós','poo-ret-os''','','inflamed, i.e. (by implication) feverish (as noun,  fever)',':--fever.'),
('G4447','G','πύρινος','pýrinos','poo''-ree-nos','','fiery, i.e. (by implication) flaming',':--of fire.'),
('G4448','G','πυρόω','pyróō','poo-ro''-o','','to kindle, i.e. (passively) to be ignited, glow  (literally), be refined (by implication), or (figuratively) to be  inflamed (with anger, grief, lust)',':--burn, fiery, be on fire, try.'),
('G4449','G','πυῤῥάζω','pyrrházō','poor-hrad''-zo','','to redden (intransitively)',':--be red.'),
('G4450','G','πυῤῥός','pyrrhós','poor-hros''','','fire-like, i.e. (specially), flame- colored',':--red.'),
('G4451','G','πύρωσις','pýrōsis','poo''-ro-sis','','ignition, i.e. (specially), smelting (figuratively,  conflagration, calamity as a test)',':--burning, trial.'),
('G4452','G','-πω','-pō','po','','an enclitic particle of  indefiniteness; yet, even; used only in the comparative. See ,  , , , .',''),
('G4453','G','πωλέω','pōléō','po-leh''-o','','to barter (as  a pedlar), i.e. to sell',':--sell, whatever is sold.'),
('G4454','G','πῶλος','pōlos','po''-los','','a "foal" or "filly", i.e. (specially), a  young ass',':--colt.'),
('G4455','G','πώποτε','pṓpote','po''-pot-e','','at any time, i.e. (with negative particle) at no  time',':--at any time, + never (…to any man),  + yet, never man.'),
('G4456','G','πωρόω','pōróō','po-ro''-o','','to petrify, i.e.  (figuratively) to indurate (render stupid or callous)',':-- blind,  harden.'),
('G4457','G','πώρωσις','pṓrōsis','po''-ro-sis','','stupidity or callousness',':--blindness, hardness.'),
('G4458','G','-πώς','-pṓs','poce','','an enclitic particle of indefiniteness  of manner; somehow or anyhow; used only in composition',':--haply, by any  (some) means, perhaps. See'),
('G4459','G','πῶς','pōs','poce','','an interrogative particle of manner; in  what way? (sometimes the question is indirect, how?); also as  exclamation, how much!',':--how, after (by) what manner (means), that.  (Occasionally unexpressed in English).'),
('G4460','G','Ῥαάβ','Rhaáb','hrah-ab''','','Raab (i.e. Rachab), a Canaanitess',':--Rahab.  See also'),
