('G5481','G','χαρακτήρ','charaktḗr','khar-ak-tare''','','a graver (the tool or the person), i.e. (by  implication) engraving (("character"), the figure stamped, i.e. an  exact copy or (figuratively) representation)',':--express image.'),
('G5482','G','χάραξ','chárax','khar''-ax','','akin to  through the idea of  scratching); a stake, i.e. (by implication) a palisade or rampart  (military mound for circumvallation in a siege)',':--trench.'),
('G5483','G','χαρίζομαι','charízomai','khar-id''-zom-ahee','','to grant as a favor, i.e. gratuitously, in  kindness, pardon or rescue',':--deliver, (frankly) forgive, (freely)  give, grant.'),
