('G5485','G','χάρις','cháris','khar''-ece','','graciousness (as gratifying), of manner or act (abstract or  concrete; literal, figurative or spiritual; especially the divine  influence upon the heart, and its reflection in the life; including  gratitude)',':--acceptable, benefit, favour, gift, grace(- ious), joy,  liberality, pleasure, thank(-s, -worthy).'),
('G5486','G','χάρισμα','chárisma','khar''-is-mah','','a (divine) gratuity, i.e. deliverance (from danger or  passion); (specially), a (spiritual) endowment, i.e. (subjectively)  religious qualification, or (objectively) miraculous faculty',':--(free)  gift.'),
('G5487','G','χαριτόω','charitóō','khar-ee-to''-o','','to grace, i.e. indue with special honor',':--make accepted, be  highly favoured.'),
